1
00:00:37,241 --> 00:00:38,641
Niagara Falls.

2
00:00:38,761 --> 00:00:42,361
Is there a better demonstration
of the sheer power of Nature?

3
00:00:43,481 --> 00:00:45,121
When I first saw this view,

4
00:00:45,241 --> 00:00:48,441
I was inspired to build
my Niagara Generator,

5
00:00:48,561 --> 00:00:51,921
and now these waters
power a city.

6
00:00:53,321 --> 00:00:55,681
But there's so much more
in Nature

7
00:00:55,801 --> 00:00:58,161
that cannot be seen
by the naked eye,

8
00:00:58,281 --> 00:01:02,121
forces invisible to us
which animate the universe.

9
00:01:02,241 --> 00:01:06,321
And they were hidden from
our understanding...until now.

10
00:01:07,721 --> 00:01:11,201
Gentlemen, I, Nikola Tesla,

11
00:01:11,321 --> 00:01:14,681
have invited you here
to pull back the curtain.

12
00:01:17,121 --> 00:01:18,161
Shall we begin?

13
00:01:19,761 --> 00:01:21,001
Observe,

14
00:01:21,121 --> 00:01:23,281
- ladies and gentlemen.
- (CROWD GASPS)

15
00:01:25,201 --> 00:01:27,481
I plan to harness
these forces of Nature

16
00:01:27,601 --> 00:01:29,921
on a scale never seen before.

17
00:01:33,761 --> 00:01:35,881
A world wireless system.

18
00:01:37,041 --> 00:01:40,681
A way for each of us to reach
beyond our immediate sphere

19
00:01:40,801 --> 00:01:43,521
into every corner of the Earth.

20
00:01:43,641 --> 00:01:45,281
(APPLAUSE)

21
00:01:45,401 --> 00:01:49,401
I only require the small
investment of $50,000.

22
00:01:49,521 --> 00:01:51,841
$50,0007?

23
00:01:51,961 --> 00:01:52,921
A small price to pay

24
00:01:53,041 --> 00:01:56,121
to transmit energy through
the ether with no wires.

25
00:01:56,241 --> 00:01:58,241
You mean flying around
in the air?

26
00:01:58,361 --> 00:02:00,721
Poppycock! They're even more
far-fetched than those

27
00:02:00,841 --> 00:02:02,561
Mars stories that we've all
been hearing about.

28
00:02:02,681 --> 00:02:04,201
I'm sure you gentlemen
know better than to believe

29
00:02:04,321 --> 00:02:05,441
everything you read

30
00:02:05,561 --> 00:02:07,161
- in the 7imes.
- Thank you, Miss Skerritt,

31
00:02:07,281 --> 00:02:09,361
but I did in fact receive
a feeble electrical signal,

32
00:02:09,481 --> 00:02:12,601
and I calculate
it comes from Mars.

33
00:02:12,721 --> 00:02:14,241
(CROWD MURMURS)

34
00:02:14,361 --> 00:02:17,961
But that's not the focus
of this project.

35
00:02:18,081 --> 00:02:22,081
Mr Tesla, I'm not in the habit
of investing in fairy tales.

36
00:02:22,201 --> 00:02:23,441
Good day to you.

37
00:02:23,561 --> 00:02:27,441
Mr Brady, sir, please!
My work is not a fairy...tale.

38
00:02:30,361 --> 00:02:33,401
I promise you,
within about a year,

39
00:02:33,521 --> 00:02:35,841
my Wardenclyffe project will be
as real and functioning

40
00:02:35,961 --> 00:02:37,721
as this very generator!

41
00:02:37,841 --> 00:02:40,041
- (CLANG)
- (ELECTRICAL SPARKING)

42
00:02:41,521 --> 00:02:43,201
Mr Tesla?

43
00:02:44,241 --> 00:02:45,721
We have an emergency.

44
00:02:52,441 --> 00:02:54,601
Oh, dear. How did this happen?

45
00:02:54,721 --> 00:02:56,921
I think an electric shock,
miss.

46
00:02:57,041 --> 00:02:58,721
What?

47
00:02:58,841 --> 00:03:00,881
One of these machines must have
killed him.

48
00:03:01,001 --> 00:03:02,201
That's impossible.

49
00:03:02,321 --> 00:03:04,841
All the apparatus here
is perfectly safe.

50
00:03:04,961 --> 00:03:08,601
Nonetheless, Mr Tesla will be
happy to take a look.

51
00:03:08,721 --> 00:03:10,121
After all, we can't have people
thinking

52
00:03:10,241 --> 00:03:12,801
there's some deadly flaw
in your designs.

53
00:03:12,921 --> 00:03:14,561
Can we, sir?

54
00:03:15,761 --> 00:03:17,601
Very well.

55
00:03:17,721 --> 00:03:19,801
I work alone!

56
00:03:35,801 --> 00:03:37,001
(CLANG)

57
00:03:37,121 --> 00:03:38,641
Ah, Miss Skerritt!

58
00:03:38,761 --> 00:03:40,561
I have solved the riddle!

59
00:03:40,681 --> 00:03:43,121
Of course there is no flaw
with my machinery.

60
00:03:43,241 --> 00:03:45,041
(LAUGHS) Parts are missing.

61
00:03:45,161 --> 00:03:46,761
We have a thief at work!

62
00:03:51,001 --> 00:03:52,601
Miss Skerritt?

63
00:04:03,241 --> 00:04:04,361
Hello?

64
00:04:05,441 --> 00:04:07,001
Anybody there?

65
00:04:16,881 --> 00:04:18,761
(HIGH-PITCHED BURBLING)

66
00:04:24,241 --> 00:04:25,881
Incredible.

67
00:04:30,721 --> 00:04:32,201
- What is it?
- (GASPS)

68
00:04:33,241 --> 00:04:34,681
I...I have no idea.

69
00:04:34,801 --> 00:04:35,801
(CLANG)

70
00:04:35,921 --> 00:04:37,841
(GASPS) I thought the foreman
went home.

71
00:04:37,961 --> 00:04:41,321
Miss Skerritt, we need to leave
now.

72
00:04:41,441 --> 00:04:44,241
(MISS SKERRITT GASPS)

73
00:04:48,201 --> 00:04:49,761
It's locked!

74
00:04:49,881 --> 00:04:51,881
- (FOOTSTEPS CLANG)
- There!

75
00:04:58,481 --> 00:04:59,521
Oh. Hi!

76
00:04:59,641 --> 00:05:02,001
I don't suppose you've seen
anything weird around here?

77
00:05:02,121 --> 00:05:03,801
Agh! I'll take that as a yes.

78
00:05:03,921 --> 00:05:05,121
Mind if I join you?

79
00:05:05,241 --> 00:05:07,121
(GASPS)

80
00:05:09,681 --> 00:05:10,881
It's Mr Brady.

81
00:05:11,001 --> 00:05:13,241
Why would a potential investor
be shooting at us?

82
00:05:13,361 --> 00:05:15,521
More urgently - who shot him?

83
00:05:16,521 --> 00:05:17,441
Run!

84
00:05:17,561 --> 00:05:18,601
TESLA: Who are you?

85
00:05:18,721 --> 00:05:20,801
Someone with a fast way
out of here!

86
00:05:20,921 --> 00:05:24,521
(TRAIN WHISTLE BLOWS)

87
00:05:24,641 --> 00:05:27,321
(GASPS) Here we go -
perfect getaway vehicle!

88
00:05:27,441 --> 00:05:29,241
Full speed,
straight to New York.

89
00:05:29,361 --> 00:05:31,201
What did I say?

90
00:05:31,321 --> 00:05:33,401
Night train, right on schedule.

91
00:05:33,521 --> 00:05:34,481
Did you find out

92
00:05:34,601 --> 00:05:36,041
what was causing
this energy thing, then?

93
00:05:36,161 --> 00:05:37,801
No, but I found these two.

94
00:05:39,041 --> 00:05:41,961
Welcome aboard the Orient
Express! We travel in style.

95
00:05:42,081 --> 00:05:45,161
This is Graham, Yaz and Ryan.
We were doing the sights

96
00:05:45,281 --> 00:05:46,801
when I picked up
a funny energy reading.

97
00:05:46,921 --> 00:05:48,001
Thought I'd check it out.

98
00:05:48,121 --> 00:05:49,561
Ran into a tiny bit of trouble
at the plant.

99
00:05:49,681 --> 00:05:51,881
Nothing to worry about.
We've lost them.

100
00:05:52,001 --> 00:05:53,081
So, here we are.

101
00:05:53,201 --> 00:05:54,801
I'm the Doctor, by the way.

102
00:05:54,921 --> 00:05:57,641
Why don't you tell me who you
are and who's shooting at you?

103
00:05:57,761 --> 00:05:59,601
Dorothy. Dorothy Skerritt.

104
00:06:00,721 --> 00:06:04,201
I am Nikola Tesla, and
I assure you I have no idea.

105
00:06:04,321 --> 00:06:05,721
Tesla!

106
00:06:05,841 --> 00:06:07,681
I knew you looked familiar!

107
00:06:07,801 --> 00:06:09,161
It's only Nikola Tesla!

108
00:06:09,281 --> 00:06:11,001
- Who?
- Nicholas something.

109
00:06:11,121 --> 00:06:12,481
Total genius!

110
00:06:12,601 --> 00:06:14,521
I always wanted to meet you!

111
00:06:14,641 --> 00:06:16,081
Shame you're a big, fat liar.

112
00:06:16,201 --> 00:06:17,761
- Pardon?
- (ALL GASP)

113
00:06:17,881 --> 00:06:19,081
YAZ: Doctor!

114
00:06:19,201 --> 00:06:20,161
And we're off again!

115
00:06:20,281 --> 00:06:22,441
Look out! Go, go, go!

116
00:06:22,561 --> 00:06:25,081
- RYAN: Who's that?
- I don't know! (GASPS)

117
00:06:25,201 --> 00:06:27,601
- (SCREWDRIVER BUZZES)
- Locked it! Keep going!

118
00:06:32,801 --> 00:06:34,481
Go!

119
00:06:34,601 --> 00:06:35,761
- No way!
- Go on, Ryan!

120
00:06:35,881 --> 00:06:38,481
- You've got this!
- Agh!

121
00:06:38,601 --> 00:06:39,721
(GASPS)

122
00:06:39,841 --> 00:06:42,481
(GRUNTS)

123
00:06:44,961 --> 00:06:46,841
It's quiet.

124
00:06:46,961 --> 00:06:49,001
Why has it gone quiet?

125
00:06:49,121 --> 00:06:51,241
(CREAKING)

126
00:06:55,961 --> 00:06:56,881
(SCREAMS)

127
00:07:00,161 --> 00:07:01,441
(SCREWDRIVER BUZZES)

128
00:07:01,561 --> 00:07:03,161
I'll take that!

129
00:07:03,281 --> 00:07:04,721
(GASPS)

130
00:07:04,841 --> 00:07:06,361
Keep it moving, then.

131
00:07:11,921 --> 00:07:13,041
Missing something?

132
00:07:21,241 --> 00:07:23,041
Come on! Argh!
It's rusted together.

133
00:07:23,161 --> 00:07:25,201
Got you!

134
00:07:31,601 --> 00:07:33,041
(LOW GROWL)

135
00:07:36,881 --> 00:07:40,121
Silurian blaster.
Nasty. Deadly thing.

136
00:07:40,241 --> 00:07:41,441
But here's the funny part -

137
00:07:41,561 --> 00:07:44,441
whatever was firing it wasn't
Silurian. So, Nikola Tesla,

138
00:07:44,561 --> 00:07:47,001
why is someone chasing you
with an alien gun?

139
00:07:47,121 --> 00:07:48,561
You believe this is alien?

140
00:07:48,681 --> 00:07:50,441
Not so fast, you big, fat liar.

141
00:07:50,561 --> 00:07:51,721
Why do you keep saying that?

142
00:07:51,841 --> 00:07:53,001
Is she always this impertinent?

143
00:07:53,121 --> 00:07:54,881
- OTHERS: Yes.
- First thing I asked you,

144
00:07:55,001 --> 00:07:56,961
I said, "Have you seen
anything weird?"

145
00:07:57,081 --> 00:07:59,241
And there's one important thing
you've failed to mention.

146
00:07:59,361 --> 00:08:00,841
See, I started this evening

147
00:08:00,961 --> 00:08:02,961
chasing an unusual
energy reading.

148
00:08:03,081 --> 00:08:05,281
I followed that signal,
loud and clear,

149
00:08:05,401 --> 00:08:06,881
to the Niagara Generator.

150
00:08:07,001 --> 00:08:11,601
So why am I still detecting it
on board this train with you?

151
00:08:11,721 --> 00:08:14,681
Whatever it is, hand it over.

152
00:08:14,801 --> 00:08:16,521
This is one of the most
miraculous things

153
00:08:16,641 --> 00:08:17,721
I've seen in my life.

154
00:08:17,841 --> 00:08:19,521
It's a mystery
I intend to solve.

155
00:08:19,641 --> 00:08:22,681
And I have no intention of
handing it to total strangers.

156
00:08:22,801 --> 00:08:24,161
Strangers who just
saved your life.

157
00:08:24,281 --> 00:08:26,521
Whatever you found
is putting you in danger.

158
00:08:26,641 --> 00:08:29,401
Yeah. Both of you.
You all right with that?

159
00:08:32,441 --> 00:08:34,281
I agree with Mr Tesla.

160
00:08:34,401 --> 00:08:37,801
If anyone can make sense
of this, it's him.

161
00:08:40,241 --> 00:08:43,241
Well, then,
if you won't hand it over,

162
00:08:43,361 --> 00:08:45,841
you leave us no choice.

163
00:08:48,921 --> 00:08:51,001
We're not letting you
out of our sights

164
00:08:51,121 --> 00:08:52,721
until we've worked this out.

165
00:08:55,881 --> 00:08:58,521
So, where's this lab, then?

166
00:09:07,481 --> 00:09:09,681
DOCTOR: Now, this is
a bit of all right.

167
00:09:09,801 --> 00:09:11,281
Gilded Age, New York!

168
00:09:11,401 --> 00:09:13,921
This is when the modern world
begins!

169
00:09:14,041 --> 00:09:17,121
New ideas, new technologies,
new skyscrapers.

170
00:09:17,241 --> 00:09:19,521
More people getting rich quick,

171
00:09:19,641 --> 00:09:21,721
and more poor people
than ever before.

172
00:09:21,841 --> 00:09:24,201
I always wanted to visit
New York, see Times Square.

173
00:09:24,321 --> 00:09:25,761
Yeah, bit early for that.

174
00:09:25,881 --> 00:09:27,241
- Empire State Building?
- Not yet.

175
00:09:27,361 --> 00:09:28,481
- Central Park?
- Yeah!

176
00:09:28,601 --> 00:09:30,361
Now, that has been around
for ages.

177
00:09:30,481 --> 00:09:32,161
- (CHANTING)
- RYAN: Can you hear yelling?

178
00:09:32,281 --> 00:09:34,121
CROWD: No to the death current,
no AC!

179
00:09:34,241 --> 00:09:36,681
No to the death current, no AC!

180
00:09:36,801 --> 00:09:39,721
No to the death current, no AC!

181
00:09:39,841 --> 00:09:41,401
Who are they?

182
00:09:41,521 --> 00:09:43,001
Protesters.

183
00:09:43,121 --> 00:09:44,761
What are they protesting about?

184
00:09:44,881 --> 00:09:47,121
- Me.
- There he is!

185
00:09:47,241 --> 00:09:49,761
Do you have any idea
what you're doing?

186
00:09:49,881 --> 00:09:51,601
- Shame on you!
- He's dangerous!

187
00:09:51,721 --> 00:09:53,401
- Go back to Mars!
- How many more people

188
00:09:53,521 --> 00:09:55,641
have to die before you admit
your machines aren't safe?

189
00:09:55,761 --> 00:09:57,761
My inventions never hurt
anyone!

190
00:09:57,881 --> 00:09:59,201
Isn't it true your last
invention caused an earthquake?

191
00:09:59,321 --> 00:10:01,041
Those were only mild tremors.

192
00:10:01,161 --> 00:10:03,201
Why are you building weapons
on Long Island?

193
00:10:03,321 --> 00:10:04,401
Mr Tesla isn't building
any kind of weapon,

194
00:10:04,521 --> 00:10:06,041
or going to answer
any questions!

195
00:10:06,161 --> 00:10:07,201
- Excuse me!
- Foreign lunatic!

196
00:10:07,321 --> 00:10:08,841
You don't belong in America.

197
00:10:08,961 --> 00:10:10,001
Yeah!

198
00:10:11,881 --> 00:10:13,441
I am an American citizen!

199
00:10:14,681 --> 00:10:18,281
And you are trespassing
in front of my lab.

200
00:10:24,001 --> 00:10:25,361
Me? A lunatic?

201
00:10:25,481 --> 00:10:27,401
They wouldn't recognise genius
if it hit them in the face.

202
00:10:27,521 --> 00:10:29,561
YAZ: Are you all right?

203
00:10:29,681 --> 00:10:32,081
Oh. Absolutely - yeah.

204
00:10:32,201 --> 00:10:33,961
Their opinions
do not affect me.

205
00:10:37,681 --> 00:10:39,241
(DISTANT CLATTERING)

206
00:10:40,801 --> 00:10:42,281
He'll just be a moment.

207
00:10:42,401 --> 00:10:43,521
(CLATTERING)

208
00:10:43,641 --> 00:10:45,201
Why don't you go on through?

209
00:10:47,961 --> 00:10:49,921
Tesla's lab.

210
00:10:50,041 --> 00:10:51,561
This is gonna be
something special!

211
00:10:57,721 --> 00:10:59,121
I won't lie.

212
00:10:59,241 --> 00:11:01,121
I was expecting more.

213
00:11:02,201 --> 00:11:03,801
Well, let's have a look about.

214
00:11:04,761 --> 00:11:06,281
Mm.

215
00:11:06,401 --> 00:11:09,241
So, Tesla - is he something
to do with the cars, then?

216
00:11:09,361 --> 00:11:10,601
Yeah, well,
they're named after him.

217
00:11:10,721 --> 00:11:12,681
He's a famous inventor,
ain't he, Doc?

218
00:11:12,801 --> 00:11:14,321
Yeah?

219
00:11:14,441 --> 00:11:16,401
And what did he invent?

220
00:11:17,641 --> 00:11:19,881
Well, he invented the, erm...

221
00:11:21,241 --> 00:11:22,801
The whatchamacallit.
Tell 'em, Doc.

222
00:11:22,921 --> 00:11:23,841
(YAZ LAUGHS)

223
00:11:23,961 --> 00:11:29,161
Nikola Tesla dreams up the
20th century before it happens.

224
00:11:29,281 --> 00:11:32,481
Before you have X-rays,
Tesla has shadowgraphs.

225
00:11:32,601 --> 00:11:34,881
Before you have drones,
Tesla has automatons.

226
00:11:35,001 --> 00:11:38,201
Before Marconi gets
the patent for radio,

227
00:11:38,321 --> 00:11:41,641
they have to take it from Tesla
because he invents it first!

228
00:11:41,761 --> 00:11:44,881
His work
on alternating currents

229
00:11:45,001 --> 00:11:48,241
helps electrify the world.

230
00:11:48,361 --> 00:11:50,441
He should have been
the first billionaire by now

231
00:11:50,561 --> 00:11:52,281
if he hadn't have
torn up his contract.

232
00:11:52,401 --> 00:11:53,921
Business isn't
his strong point.

233
00:11:56,561 --> 00:11:57,841
Doctor.

234
00:12:01,361 --> 00:12:03,561
I believe you wanted
to see this.

235
00:12:03,681 --> 00:12:05,081
(FIZZING)

236
00:12:07,561 --> 00:12:09,841
Is this what you found
in the generator?

237
00:12:09,961 --> 00:12:12,321
Giving off all that energy -
but why?

238
00:12:14,001 --> 00:12:15,721
- (SPHERE BUZZES)
- Whoa!

239
00:12:18,761 --> 00:12:21,281
You see how it moves
independently?

240
00:12:21,401 --> 00:12:24,241
I believe this is something I
like to call "remote control”.

241
00:12:24,361 --> 00:12:26,041
Remote control?
You came up with that?

242
00:12:26,161 --> 00:12:29,041
I believe this is operating
on a similar principle.

243
00:12:29,161 --> 00:12:31,081
If we could just
work out its purpose...

244
00:12:31,201 --> 00:12:32,641
I know what it is.

245
00:12:33,801 --> 00:12:35,001
It's an Orb of Thassor.

246
00:12:35,121 --> 00:12:37,401
But I've no idea
what it's doing here.

247
00:12:43,241 --> 00:12:45,161
The Thassor were
one of the ancient races.

248
00:12:45,281 --> 00:12:48,241
Amazing storytellers.
Inventors, explorers.

249
00:12:48,361 --> 00:12:51,641
They built these orbs as a way
to spread information,

250
00:12:51,761 --> 00:12:55,961
to send out among the stars
as a way to share their legacy

251
00:12:56,081 --> 00:12:57,681
long after they were gone.

252
00:12:58,721 --> 00:13:01,201
Why would someone try to kill
us to get their hands on that?

253
00:13:02,361 --> 00:13:04,201
I've no idea.

254
00:13:04,321 --> 00:13:05,561
- (BUZZING STOPS)
- But maybe I can find out.

255
00:13:05,681 --> 00:13:06,841
(SCREWDRIVER BUZZES)

256
00:13:08,921 --> 00:13:10,241
I think it's been repurposed.

257
00:13:10,361 --> 00:13:12,481
But I can't work out
what it's doing instead.

258
00:13:12,601 --> 00:13:14,801
This is all wrong!
Something this elegant

259
00:13:14,921 --> 00:13:17,121
shouldn't be giving off
this kind of noise.

260
00:13:17,241 --> 00:13:19,161
Its energy readings
are off the charts!

261
00:13:20,281 --> 00:13:23,441
That instrument detects energy?
Is-Is it your own design?

262
00:13:23,561 --> 00:13:25,761
I made it!
Mainly out of spoons.

263
00:13:25,881 --> 00:13:27,721
You're an inventor!

264
00:13:27,841 --> 00:13:29,121
I have my moments.

265
00:13:29,241 --> 00:13:30,401
I knew it!

266
00:13:30,521 --> 00:13:32,881
So... So you can understand
how it feels -

267
00:13:33,001 --> 00:13:36,081
you know, when you have an idea
and-and to make it real.

268
00:13:36,201 --> 00:13:38,161
I don't think
there's any greater thrill!

269
00:13:39,401 --> 00:13:40,961
I couldn't agree more.

270
00:13:43,401 --> 00:13:44,801
You... You spoke of aliens.

271
00:13:44,921 --> 00:13:47,081
People - you know -
laugh at the very idea!

272
00:13:47,201 --> 00:13:49,001
- But not you.
- Well, apparently,

273
00:13:49,121 --> 00:13:50,361
I'm not like other people.

274
00:13:50,481 --> 00:13:53,201
It can be difficult, you know,

275
00:13:53,321 --> 00:13:55,841
to feel no-one else
sees the world the way you do.

276
00:13:55,961 --> 00:13:57,241
It's like you're, er...

277
00:13:57,361 --> 00:13:58,961
Out of place.

278
00:14:00,001 --> 00:14:01,681
Yeah.

279
00:14:03,161 --> 00:14:06,641
I... I thought... I thought
things would be different.

280
00:14:06,761 --> 00:14:09,401
You know, when I first arrived
in America,

281
00:14:09,521 --> 00:14:12,041
I had four cents to my name -
I was robbed on the journey -

282
00:14:12,161 --> 00:14:14,721
but still I thought,
"This is the beginning!”

283
00:14:14,841 --> 00:14:16,561
Here I would prosper,
my ideas would live!

284
00:14:16,681 --> 00:14:19,761
Changing the world takes time.
You have to be patient.

285
00:14:19,881 --> 00:14:22,561
I try.
But you saw them outside.

286
00:14:22,681 --> 00:14:27,001
They... They talk as if I was
dangerous or mad, or...

287
00:14:27,121 --> 00:14:29,361
So prove them wrong!

288
00:14:29,481 --> 00:14:30,841
(DOOR OPENS)

289
00:14:30,961 --> 00:14:34,921
Sir, this was just delivered -
it's from Mr Morgan.

290
00:14:36,441 --> 00:14:37,801
Excellent.

291
00:14:39,041 --> 00:14:42,961
Mr Morgan is the investor
behind my Wardenclyffe project.

292
00:14:43,081 --> 00:14:44,801
With his help, we...

293
00:14:52,841 --> 00:14:54,921
- He's pulling the funding.
- DOROTHY: What?

294
00:14:56,281 --> 00:15:00,161
I, er...can't complete
Wardenclyffe without it.

295
00:15:00,281 --> 00:15:02,241
I'm never gonna be able
to prove it works.

296
00:15:02,361 --> 00:15:04,921
- (FLASH BULB POPS)
- Who's that?

297
00:15:05,041 --> 00:15:06,241
(SCREWDRIVER BUZZES)

298
00:15:06,361 --> 00:15:09,121
That was Harold Green -
one of Edison's men.

299
00:15:09,241 --> 00:15:11,161
YAZ: As in Thomas Edison?

300
00:15:11,281 --> 00:15:12,481
- Light-bulb guy?
- All right.

301
00:15:12,601 --> 00:15:15,041
We all know Edison. It's Tesla
you've never heard of.

302
00:15:15,161 --> 00:15:16,121
He's literally
standing right there.

303
00:15:16,241 --> 00:15:17,561
Yeah - sorry, son.

304
00:15:17,681 --> 00:15:20,281
Edison, Edison.
Of course it's Edison.

305
00:15:20,401 --> 00:15:22,721
He's plagued me
every step of my career!

306
00:15:22,841 --> 00:15:25,001
Edison champions a rival form
of electric current

307
00:15:25,121 --> 00:15:26,481
to Mr Tesla's AC.

308
00:15:26,601 --> 00:15:28,401
Direct current - of course,
he would champion

309
00:15:28,521 --> 00:15:30,041
something so slow
and inefficient.

310
00:15:30,161 --> 00:15:33,001
TESLA: That man
is a liar and a thief.

311
00:15:33,121 --> 00:15:36,161
Are we saying Thomas Edison
is after the Orb of Thassor?

312
00:15:36,281 --> 00:15:38,481
Don't be daft - how's Edison's
men gonna get their hands on

313
00:15:38,601 --> 00:15:40,561
a Slymurian laser blaster?

314
00:15:40,681 --> 00:15:42,441
Silurian.
Let's go and find out.

315
00:15:42,561 --> 00:15:44,481
You three stay here
and guard the Orb.

316
00:15:44,601 --> 00:15:46,521
You two - with me.

317
00:15:46,641 --> 00:15:48,481
Time we paid a visit
to Mr Thomas Edison.

318
00:15:50,641 --> 00:15:52,921
Ladies and gentlemen,

319
00:15:53,041 --> 00:15:56,641
AC is the most deadly force
known to science.

320
00:15:56,761 --> 00:15:58,721
For the public's safety,

321
00:15:58,841 --> 00:16:01,401
the Niagara Generator
should be shut down.

322
00:16:01,521 --> 00:16:02,801
DOCTOR: And let me guess.

323
00:16:03,841 --> 00:16:06,001
An Edison Generator
built in its place.

324
00:16:06,121 --> 00:16:07,641
Couldn't have
put it better myself.

325
00:16:07,761 --> 00:16:09,441
Thomas Edison, we need to talk.

326
00:16:09,561 --> 00:16:11,121
- As I was saying...
- We could talk here

327
00:16:11,241 --> 00:16:12,801
but I think you'd prefer to go
somewhere more private.

328
00:16:12,921 --> 00:16:14,321
You want to make
an appointment,

329
00:16:14,441 --> 00:16:15,361
speak to my secretary.

330
00:16:15,481 --> 00:16:16,641
Alien weapons.

331
00:16:17,881 --> 00:16:19,281
How are you getting
your hands on them?

332
00:16:19,401 --> 00:16:21,641
(CHUCKLES) Alien weapons.

333
00:16:21,761 --> 00:16:23,521
You have the wrong inventor,
ma'am.

334
00:16:23,641 --> 00:16:27,561
It's Nikola Tesla's
been talking to Mars.

335
00:16:27,681 --> 00:16:29,201
I keep my feet on the ground.

336
00:16:29,321 --> 00:16:31,881
So...you don't recognise this?

337
00:16:36,241 --> 00:16:38,121
Let's take this inside.

338
00:16:39,761 --> 00:16:42,521
GRAHAM: Whoa! This is
some set-up he's got.

339
00:16:42,641 --> 00:16:44,121
See, this guy
I've definitely heard of -

340
00:16:44,241 --> 00:16:45,921
he's got to be America's
most famous inventor.

341
00:16:46,041 --> 00:16:48,481
Yeah. But not exactly
a shrinking violet, is he?

342
00:16:48,601 --> 00:16:50,321
I mean, he's plastered his name
all over the shop!

343
00:16:50,441 --> 00:16:52,521
Talk about
tooting your own horn!

344
00:16:53,881 --> 00:16:57,521
I have never seen
anything like this in my life.

345
00:16:57,641 --> 00:16:58,681
Is it your design?

346
00:16:59,721 --> 00:17:00,921
Who has the patent?

347
00:17:01,041 --> 00:17:02,281
This isn't
a business opportunity -

348
00:17:02,401 --> 00:17:03,481
someone tried to
shoot us with it

349
00:17:03,601 --> 00:17:05,521
just before we caught
an employee of yours

350
00:17:05,641 --> 00:17:07,001
spying on Nikola Tesla.

351
00:17:07,121 --> 00:17:08,321
Someone's trying
to steal from him,

352
00:17:08,441 --> 00:17:09,601
and he seems
pretty sure it's you.

353
00:17:09,721 --> 00:17:11,121
Does he, now?

354
00:17:12,121 --> 00:17:13,361
Ma'am,

355
00:17:13,481 --> 00:17:16,201
I may keep an eye on my rivals,
but I do not steal.

356
00:17:16,321 --> 00:17:17,841
I have no need to.

357
00:17:19,601 --> 00:17:22,121
There are a thousand patents
in the Edison name.

358
00:17:22,241 --> 00:17:24,041
You might have seen it
on the building.

359
00:17:24,161 --> 00:17:26,881
- That's not how Tesla sees it.
- He's sore about the past.

360
00:17:27,001 --> 00:17:28,241
You know, I gave him a job

361
00:17:28,361 --> 00:17:30,121
when he first arrived
in this country

362
00:17:30,241 --> 00:17:31,881
on the factory floor.

363
00:17:32,001 --> 00:17:34,841
He ended up digging ditches
for two bucks a day.

364
00:17:34,961 --> 00:17:36,441
Tesla?!

365
00:17:36,561 --> 00:17:38,761
Dapper dude
who dresses for the opera?

366
00:17:38,881 --> 00:17:40,481
How did he end up
digging a ditch?

367
00:17:40,601 --> 00:17:42,401
He heard me say I'd pay $50,000

368
00:17:42,521 --> 00:17:44,761
to the man who could
fix my generator.

369
00:17:46,281 --> 00:17:50,041
He worked on that thing
day and night for a year.

370
00:17:50,161 --> 00:17:51,201
And he did it.

371
00:17:51,321 --> 00:17:54,241
And you, being
the upstanding businessman,

372
00:17:54,361 --> 00:17:55,761
paid every last cent,
I presume.

373
00:17:55,881 --> 00:17:58,481
I offered him a ten-buck raise.

374
00:17:58,601 --> 00:18:00,561
He quit and chose to dig.

375
00:18:01,601 --> 00:18:04,521
Man just didn't understand
the American sense of humour.

376
00:18:19,841 --> 00:18:21,441
I thought you'd have
more stuff.

377
00:18:21,561 --> 00:18:24,841
Sketches, blueprints, you know.
For all your inventions.

378
00:18:25,881 --> 00:18:27,881
All in here. (SIGHS)

379
00:18:28,001 --> 00:18:30,361
Before anything else, I...

380
00:18:30,481 --> 00:18:32,321
...I build things here.

381
00:18:37,201 --> 00:18:38,961
Tell me about
this Wardenclyffe project.

382
00:18:42,121 --> 00:18:43,361
Er...

383
00:18:44,481 --> 00:18:46,761
Imagine if, er...

384
00:18:46,881 --> 00:18:49,961
...wherever you were,
you were able to hear music

385
00:18:50,081 --> 00:18:53,281
or, er, the speech
of a great leader, or, er...

386
00:18:53,401 --> 00:18:56,201
...conjure a map
of what lay beyond.

387
00:18:56,321 --> 00:18:58,241
That's what I propose
with Wardenclyffe -

388
00:18:58,361 --> 00:19:00,841
all of human knowledge
shared freely.

389
00:19:00,961 --> 00:19:02,761
Now that sounds
like the future.

390
00:19:03,841 --> 00:19:05,441
Yeah. Yeah...

391
00:19:05,561 --> 00:19:07,361
It will change the world.

392
00:19:09,041 --> 00:19:10,601
Why can't anyone else see that?

393
00:19:11,641 --> 00:19:14,441
There must be someone
who'll invest in it.

394
00:19:14,561 --> 00:19:17,201
Well, if there is,
I can't find them,

395
00:19:17,321 --> 00:19:19,881
and, er, without the money,
I have no power source,

396
00:19:20,001 --> 00:19:21,321
and without power...

397
00:19:21,441 --> 00:19:23,721
(ORB BUZZES)

398
00:19:27,161 --> 00:19:28,681
SCIENTIST: Sir,
if you'll just permit me...

399
00:19:28,801 --> 00:19:32,521
No! No, the grounding coil
goes in separately.

400
00:19:38,561 --> 00:19:39,721
- I said don't touch!
- SCIENTIST: Sorry.

401
00:19:40,761 --> 00:19:42,881
Really? Go over there!

402
00:19:49,441 --> 00:19:51,601
(CRACKLING)

403
00:19:52,681 --> 00:19:54,121
(GASPING)

404
00:19:57,641 --> 00:19:58,961
(LOUD CRACKLING)

405
00:20:03,801 --> 00:20:05,801
(LOW GROWLING)

406
00:20:08,681 --> 00:20:10,241
(METAL CLATTERS)

407
00:20:13,121 --> 00:20:14,401
Something's wrong.

408
00:20:14,521 --> 00:20:15,961
Oh, I should say.

409
00:20:16,081 --> 00:20:18,161
We've done this dance
for long enough.

410
00:20:18,281 --> 00:20:20,121
Now, what have you done
with my man, huh?

411
00:20:22,481 --> 00:20:25,481
Oh, don't play dumb.
He was keeping tabs

412
00:20:25,601 --> 00:20:28,641
on that dog-and-pony show
of Tesla's at Niagara.

413
00:20:28,761 --> 00:20:31,641
Now he's gone quiet -
the very day you show up

414
00:20:31,761 --> 00:20:32,961
pointing the finger.

415
00:20:33,081 --> 00:20:34,721
Huh?

416
00:20:34,841 --> 00:20:36,561
Trust me, Mr Edison -

417
00:20:36,681 --> 00:20:38,641
we're not the people
you should be worried about.

418
00:20:38,761 --> 00:20:39,761
He is.

419
00:20:40,801 --> 00:20:42,361
DOCTOR: behind me!

420
00:20:42,481 --> 00:20:44,321
Harold? What's the matter
with him?

421
00:20:44,441 --> 00:20:46,361
That's not Harold Green.

422
00:20:47,641 --> 00:20:50,081
No human readings.
What is that? Not possession.

423
00:20:50,201 --> 00:20:52,441
Psionic image cloaking?
Hologram?

424
00:20:52,561 --> 00:20:54,081
EDISON:
What are you talking about?

425
00:20:54,201 --> 00:20:55,721
- (GROWLING)
- No guns, Ryan!

426
00:20:55,841 --> 00:20:57,441
Whatever you are,
whatever you've come for,

427
00:20:57,561 --> 00:20:58,881
nobody else needs to get hurt.

428
00:20:59,001 --> 00:21:00,841
- (GROWLS)
- DOCTOR: Desk!

429
00:21:00,961 --> 00:21:01,961
Run!

430
00:21:05,121 --> 00:21:06,561
EDISON: Oh, my God.

431
00:21:06,681 --> 00:21:07,721
No time.

432
00:21:07,841 --> 00:21:09,041
This way.

433
00:21:11,481 --> 00:21:13,121
DOCTOR: In here.

434
00:21:13,241 --> 00:21:14,481
GRAHAM: Doc, look!

435
00:21:14,601 --> 00:21:15,641
(DOOR CLOSES)

436
00:21:15,761 --> 00:21:17,121
(SCREWDRIVER BUZZES)

437
00:21:19,161 --> 00:21:20,161
Oh, he's dead.

438
00:21:21,401 --> 00:21:22,921
He's the real Harold Green.

439
00:21:23,041 --> 00:21:25,961
Whatever's chasing us
is projecting his image

440
00:21:26,081 --> 00:21:28,761
and using it to keep
his true self hidden.

441
00:21:29,921 --> 00:21:31,921
You better not be
hiding anything.

442
00:21:32,041 --> 00:21:33,241
People have died.

443
00:21:33,361 --> 00:21:35,321
My workers!

444
00:21:35,441 --> 00:21:38,081
All those men work for me.
They had families.

445
00:21:38,201 --> 00:21:40,481
I had dinner with this guy
and his wife last week.

446
00:21:40,601 --> 00:21:42,481
I have to tell her,
tell the families.

447
00:21:42,601 --> 00:21:44,241
- Now give me the gun.
- Definitely not.

448
00:21:44,361 --> 00:21:45,401
We're not shooting it!

449
00:21:45,521 --> 00:21:47,761
We need to contain it,
work out what it wants.

450
00:21:49,641 --> 00:21:51,361
This is your chemical lab.

451
00:21:51,481 --> 00:21:52,481
Perfect!

452
00:21:54,201 --> 00:21:56,121
Ammonium nitrate,
bit of green stuff.

453
00:21:57,161 --> 00:21:58,481
- Where's your zinc?
- Zinc?

454
00:21:58,601 --> 00:21:59,881
Have you lost your damn mi...?

455
00:22:01,121 --> 00:22:02,321
Oh!

456
00:22:02,441 --> 00:22:04,481
Finally thinking
like a scientist.

457
00:22:05,841 --> 00:22:08,081
(ELECTRICITY BUZZES)

458
00:22:08,201 --> 00:22:09,841
YAZ: What is that?

459
00:22:09,961 --> 00:22:11,041
Power!

460
00:22:11,161 --> 00:22:13,641
Waiting to be harnessed.
Your-Your Doctor was right.

461
00:22:13,761 --> 00:22:16,201
The Orb is emitting
huge amounts of energy.

462
00:22:16,321 --> 00:22:19,681
It's pulsing - like a siren.
Or radar.

463
00:22:21,161 --> 00:22:22,441
Radar?

464
00:22:22,561 --> 00:22:24,521
Using energy waves to work out
what's around you.

465
00:22:26,281 --> 00:22:27,641
It's just a theory.

466
00:22:27,761 --> 00:22:30,241
I've been working on
a similar theory myself.

467
00:22:30,361 --> 00:22:32,761
I call it my exploring ray.

468
00:22:32,881 --> 00:22:34,681
But, anyway -
the Orb is emitting

469
00:22:34,801 --> 00:22:36,201
distinct waves of energy.

470
00:22:36,321 --> 00:22:39,921
It's... It's like it's, ah,
sensing its surroundings.

471
00:22:40,041 --> 00:22:41,961
YAZ: Or scanning.

472
00:22:42,081 --> 00:22:43,961
Which makes me wonder...

473
00:22:44,081 --> 00:22:45,601
What is it looking for?

474
00:22:51,361 --> 00:22:52,841
(GROWLING HISS)

475
00:23:12,321 --> 00:23:15,041
There'll be more
where that came from.

476
00:23:15,161 --> 00:23:17,801
How about we try this again?
Who are you?

477
00:23:17,921 --> 00:23:19,521
Show your true form.

478
00:23:28,121 --> 00:23:29,481
(GROWLING HISS)

479
00:23:29,601 --> 00:23:31,321
What in God's name?

480
00:23:33,241 --> 00:23:35,521
Yaz! It's not Edison!

481
00:23:35,641 --> 00:23:37,761
I mean, it was, but
it turns out it's aliens, too.

482
00:23:37,881 --> 00:23:40,681
They can look like anyone,
so don't let anyone in!

483
00:23:40,801 --> 00:23:42,321
Tell Tesla! Tell Dorothy!

484
00:23:42,441 --> 00:23:43,801
Lock every door!

485
00:23:45,721 --> 00:23:46,641
I'm sorry.

486
00:23:46,761 --> 00:23:50,321
DOCTOR: Yaz?
Yaz, are you all right?

487
00:23:50,441 --> 00:23:53,841
- You are dead.
- We know you want the Orb.

488
00:23:53,961 --> 00:23:55,681
Let her go.

489
00:23:55,801 --> 00:23:58,881
Exactly - you don't
have to hurt her.

490
00:23:59,921 --> 00:24:01,641
With your levels of technology,

491
00:24:01,761 --> 00:24:04,241
you must understand
there is no need for violence.

492
00:24:04,361 --> 00:24:07,561
(DISTORTED)
We did not come for the Orb.

493
00:24:09,201 --> 00:24:12,041
We came for you.

494
00:24:12,161 --> 00:24:13,801
No!

495
00:24:36,641 --> 00:24:39,601
Welcome, Nikola Tesla.

496
00:24:42,521 --> 00:24:44,481
(TARDIS THRUMS)

497
00:24:48,961 --> 00:24:49,961
(GASPS)

498
00:24:50,081 --> 00:24:52,761
You're all right. You've
probably got questions.

499
00:24:52,881 --> 00:24:54,961
They took them.

500
00:24:56,401 --> 00:24:57,721
Where did they take them?

501
00:24:57,841 --> 00:24:59,681
We know they've got
cloaking tech,

502
00:24:59,801 --> 00:25:01,281
but if I rig a bypass...

503
00:25:02,561 --> 00:25:05,601
Luckily, high-speed inventing
is one of my specialisms.

504
00:25:13,321 --> 00:25:15,681
First time here can be a lot.

505
00:25:15,801 --> 00:25:18,721
It certainly is a lot.

506
00:25:18,841 --> 00:25:20,961
But you take it in your stride.

507
00:25:21,081 --> 00:25:22,921
Where do you even come from?

508
00:25:23,041 --> 00:25:25,241
Yorkshire, England.

509
00:25:25,361 --> 00:25:28,561
I was at home - you know,
normal life, work -

510
00:25:28,681 --> 00:25:31,081
then, boom... The Doctor.

511
00:25:31,201 --> 00:25:32,561
Changed my whole life.

512
00:25:32,681 --> 00:25:35,321
I was the same
before I met Mr Tesla.

513
00:25:35,441 --> 00:25:38,681
I wanted my own career -
something steady -

514
00:25:38,801 --> 00:25:42,121
then he showed me all these
discoveries that could be made.

515
00:25:42,241 --> 00:25:44,441
But it seemed like
impossible things.

516
00:25:44,561 --> 00:25:48,761
And now,
something normal, steady...

517
00:25:48,881 --> 00:25:50,081
Doesn't seem so important.

518
00:25:52,041 --> 00:25:53,841
We'll get 'em back.

519
00:25:53,961 --> 00:25:56,281
She's good at impossible, too.

520
00:25:57,641 --> 00:25:58,841
Right, then.

521
00:25:58,961 --> 00:26:00,241
(ORB BUZZES)

522
00:26:00,361 --> 00:26:01,761
On you pop.

523
00:26:04,841 --> 00:26:07,761
This is the most
extraordinary thing.

524
00:26:07,881 --> 00:26:10,881
Is it a single machine
or some kind of, er...

525
00:26:11,001 --> 00:26:12,761
...mechanical factory?

526
00:26:14,521 --> 00:26:15,761
GRAHAM: Oi!

527
00:26:15,881 --> 00:26:17,801
You're in here
strictly on the QT, right?

528
00:26:17,921 --> 00:26:19,761
So get those dollar signs
out of your eyes

529
00:26:19,881 --> 00:26:22,721
cos this little lot ain't
for sale. Copyright - her!

530
00:26:22,841 --> 00:26:23,921
That's a British accent,
isn't it?

531
00:26:24,041 --> 00:26:24,961
Yes.

532
00:26:25,081 --> 00:26:27,681
Now there's a country who's
never understood business.

533
00:26:27,801 --> 00:26:29,121
DOCTOR: Please work.

534
00:26:30,601 --> 00:26:32,441
GRAHAM: Have you
got something, Doc?

535
00:26:34,041 --> 00:26:35,201
Of course!

536
00:26:35,321 --> 00:26:37,081
That's why they left it behind.

537
00:26:37,201 --> 00:26:39,761
It's been hacked. It's not
broadcasting any more -

538
00:26:39,881 --> 00:26:41,041
it's receiving.

539
00:26:41,161 --> 00:26:43,841
GRAHAM: You mean
it's a bugging device.

540
00:26:43,961 --> 00:26:45,281
Thought so.

541
00:26:45,401 --> 00:26:46,761
Moment I saw it.

542
00:26:46,881 --> 00:26:50,521
DOCTOR: Exactly. Repurposed
from its original intent.

543
00:26:51,761 --> 00:26:54,161
It's been scanning the Earth
since it got here.

544
00:26:55,801 --> 00:26:57,441
(SCREWDRIVER BUZZES)

545
00:26:57,561 --> 00:27:00,921
And it must have finally found
what it's been looking for.

546
00:27:04,881 --> 00:27:06,481
What is this place?

547
00:27:06,601 --> 00:27:09,481
You stand on the Throne Ship
of the Skithra.

548
00:27:09,601 --> 00:27:11,761
High above your meagre city.

549
00:27:15,161 --> 00:27:17,601
You can see your city.

550
00:27:17,721 --> 00:27:20,161
But your city cannot see us.

551
00:27:22,841 --> 00:27:24,201
We have been watching,

552
00:27:24,321 --> 00:27:27,761
hidden from human eyes
while we searched.

553
00:27:27,881 --> 00:27:31,281
This is an electrical
condenser - from my generator.

554
00:27:31,401 --> 00:27:34,281
We have gathered supplies.
Now you will work.

555
00:27:35,881 --> 00:27:37,001
Work on what?

556
00:27:37,121 --> 00:27:40,241
Our ship. Our weapons.
Everything.

557
00:27:41,921 --> 00:27:43,761
They're hiding their real faces
behind projections -

558
00:27:43,881 --> 00:27:47,241
they could look like anything,
be anywhere. There's no trail!

559
00:27:47,361 --> 00:27:49,041
If we're looking for
a trail to follow,

560
00:27:49,161 --> 00:27:50,681
what if Tesla already found it?

561
00:27:50,801 --> 00:27:52,281
DOROTHY: But he did.

562
00:27:53,561 --> 00:27:54,921
The Mars signal.

563
00:27:56,281 --> 00:27:58,241
I didn't believe him -
not really.

564
00:27:58,361 --> 00:28:00,681
But he records
all his observations.

565
00:28:00,801 --> 00:28:03,121
We have to go to Wardenclyffe.

566
00:28:08,601 --> 00:28:10,681
Wow. Now, this is a lab.

567
00:28:10,801 --> 00:28:13,001
Mr Tesla started transferring
all of his work

568
00:28:13,121 --> 00:28:14,761
to Wardenclyffe months ago.

569
00:28:16,321 --> 00:28:18,841
He intercepted
the Mars signal with this.

570
00:28:19,881 --> 00:28:21,281
He calls it his Teslascope.

571
00:28:21,401 --> 00:28:22,721
Here are
all the readings he took.

572
00:28:22,841 --> 00:28:24,121
They must have increased
the cloaking

573
00:28:24,241 --> 00:28:26,161
when they realised
he'd spotted them.

574
00:28:26,281 --> 00:28:27,681
Hey! Don't take
your eyes off him,

575
00:28:27,801 --> 00:28:29,681
and don't let him
touch anything!/

576
00:28:29,801 --> 00:28:31,321
We're on Long Island.

577
00:28:32,561 --> 00:28:35,721
This box transported us
halfway across New York.

578
00:28:35,841 --> 00:28:37,281
Unbelievable.

579
00:28:37,401 --> 00:28:38,561
Yeah, well, keep it
to yourself,

580
00:28:38,681 --> 00:28:40,361
or people'll say
you're as crazy as Tesla.

581
00:28:40,481 --> 00:28:42,041
That, my friend,
will never happen.

582
00:28:42,161 --> 00:28:43,081
Yeah, still -

583
00:28:43,201 --> 00:28:44,601
bet you'd jump at the chance
to have him back working

584
00:28:44,721 --> 00:28:46,161
- for you, wouldn't you?
- Yeah?

585
00:28:46,281 --> 00:28:47,801
- Yeah!
- How'd you figure that?

586
00:28:47,921 --> 00:28:50,441
Cos I had a supervisor
like you at my old depot.

587
00:28:50,561 --> 00:28:53,961
And men like you don't pay
a bloke that much attention

588
00:28:54,081 --> 00:28:56,921
unless you think
there's a pay-out coming.

589
00:28:57,041 --> 00:28:58,601
DOCTOR:
It must be here somewhere.

590
00:28:58,721 --> 00:29:01,881
Ah, I've found it!
The signal readout.

591
00:29:02,001 --> 00:29:03,361
Now we're in business.

592
00:29:04,641 --> 00:29:06,841
One of these must be good
for getting out of here.

593
00:29:06,961 --> 00:29:08,161
Got to find a way off the ship.

594
00:29:08,281 --> 00:29:09,921
We're hundreds of feet
above New York.

595
00:29:10,041 --> 00:29:11,641
What do you suggest
we do - open a door?

596
00:29:11,761 --> 00:29:15,001
I'd suggest we don't surrender
to the giant alien scorpion.

597
00:29:16,441 --> 00:29:20,801
You're right. I'm sorry.
This is all my fault.

598
00:29:20,921 --> 00:29:22,921
You shouldn't even be here.

599
00:29:23,041 --> 00:29:24,721
Just cos you're a genius
doesn't mean

600
00:29:24,841 --> 00:29:27,001
you have to figure everything
out on your own.

601
00:29:27,121 --> 00:29:28,841
We're in this together.

602
00:29:30,721 --> 00:29:32,721
You have examined
the equipment?

603
00:29:35,361 --> 00:29:36,721
(CLEARS THROAT)

604
00:29:36,841 --> 00:29:38,441
Yes, I have.

605
00:29:38,561 --> 00:29:40,921
There are more secrets
on this ship

606
00:29:41,041 --> 00:29:43,321
than I could discover
in a lifetime. Er...

607
00:29:43,441 --> 00:29:45,601
It...
It is a scientist's dream.

608
00:29:45,721 --> 00:29:47,161
Then your work shall begin.

609
00:29:47,281 --> 00:29:48,721
You will prepare us for battle.

610
00:29:48,841 --> 00:29:49,921
No, I won't.

611
00:29:51,841 --> 00:29:53,721
(LOUD HISSING)

612
00:29:54,921 --> 00:29:57,321
Your work would burn a path
across the galaxies.

613
00:29:57,441 --> 00:29:59,081
On Earth, you are nothing.

614
00:29:59,201 --> 00:30:01,001
Perhaps I will achieve nothing,

615
00:30:01,121 --> 00:30:03,281
but if I achieve anything,

616
00:30:03,401 --> 00:30:05,121
it will be in the name
of progress,

617
00:30:05,241 --> 00:30:07,441
and you are not my idea
of progress.

618
00:30:07,561 --> 00:30:08,721
(ROARS)

619
00:30:11,601 --> 00:30:13,321
Kill the stowaway.

620
00:30:16,001 --> 00:30:17,561
I knew I had one
in my tool box.

621
00:30:18,801 --> 00:30:20,281
Braxium bouncer, mark III.

622
00:30:20,401 --> 00:30:21,681
Found it at a bazaar.

623
00:30:21,801 --> 00:30:23,921
Bit wonky, but I can't take
the TARDIS.

624
00:30:24,041 --> 00:30:26,761
This should give us
enough power to transport me,

625
00:30:26,881 --> 00:30:28,561
Yaz and Tesla back here.

626
00:30:28,681 --> 00:30:30,321
But once I'm there,

627
00:30:30,441 --> 00:30:32,761
I can't jump back
until it recharges itself.

628
00:30:32,881 --> 00:30:34,761
Which, you know,
I'm not worried about.

629
00:30:34,881 --> 00:30:37,001
Definitely. And you shouldn't
be worried about it either.

630
00:30:37,121 --> 00:30:38,441
Not in the least.

631
00:30:38,561 --> 00:30:41,161
QUEEN SKITHRA:
This is the price of refusal.

632
00:30:41,281 --> 00:30:44,001
First, she dies,
then everyone down there.

633
00:30:44,121 --> 00:30:45,561
Stop.

634
00:30:45,681 --> 00:30:47,561
She's my assistant, I need her.

635
00:30:47,681 --> 00:30:49,041
(HISSES)

636
00:30:49,161 --> 00:30:51,281
She's not important.

637
00:30:51,401 --> 00:30:53,801
DOCTOR: I'm going to
have to disagree with that.

638
00:30:53,921 --> 00:30:55,241
Ah.

639
00:30:55,361 --> 00:30:57,601
Nice place you've got here.

640
00:30:57,721 --> 00:30:59,321
Probably.

641
00:30:59,441 --> 00:31:01,881
If you cleaned up a bit.
I mean, I'm messy, but this?

642
00:31:02,001 --> 00:31:02,881
(GROWLS)

643
00:31:03,001 --> 00:31:04,281
Are you guys all right?

644
00:31:04,401 --> 00:31:05,881
Better now you're here.

645
00:31:06,001 --> 00:31:08,241
I'm the Doctor.
I don't believe we've met.

646
00:31:08,361 --> 00:31:10,121
You address
the queen of the Skithra?

647
00:31:10,241 --> 00:31:12,521
You trespass on my ship?

648
00:31:12,641 --> 00:31:14,281
Oh, is this your ship?

649
00:31:14,401 --> 00:31:16,201
Because it looks Venusian to me

650
00:31:16,321 --> 00:31:18,681
and I'm pretty sure
that's a Klendov warp drive.

651
00:31:20,281 --> 00:31:22,001
Is there a single thing
on this ship

652
00:31:22,121 --> 00:31:23,841
that you've built yourselves?

653
00:31:24,921 --> 00:31:26,761
This one is clever.

654
00:31:26,881 --> 00:31:28,441
She will assist Tesla.

655
00:31:28,561 --> 00:31:30,641
I've had worse jobs.

656
00:31:30,761 --> 00:31:32,281
Or she will die.

657
00:31:34,561 --> 00:31:36,561
Stolen tech...

658
00:31:36,681 --> 00:31:37,881
...stolen faces,

659
00:31:38,001 --> 00:31:40,441
and now all your stolen gear
is breaking down.

660
00:31:40,561 --> 00:31:41,761
And what do you do?

661
00:31:41,881 --> 00:31:44,321
Steal someone else to fix it.

662
00:31:44,441 --> 00:31:46,561
All this killing and looting!
Did it never occur to you

663
00:31:46,681 --> 00:31:49,961
to try thinking or building
something instead?

664
00:31:50,081 --> 00:31:51,001
(RASPING LAUGH)

665
00:31:51,121 --> 00:31:54,601
Why would we build when
all there is is ours to take?

666
00:31:56,041 --> 00:31:57,641
Tesla...

667
00:31:57,761 --> 00:31:58,801
Why Tesla?

668
00:31:58,921 --> 00:32:01,361
Why send the sphere
to track him,

669
00:32:01,481 --> 00:32:03,481
an inventor from 19007

670
00:32:05,201 --> 00:32:07,081
We required an engineer.

671
00:32:12,161 --> 00:32:13,641
I was talking!

672
00:32:15,521 --> 00:32:17,681
We required an engineer.

673
00:32:17,801 --> 00:32:21,041
Tesla showed superior signs
of intelligence.

674
00:32:21,161 --> 00:32:23,081
He discovered our signal.

675
00:32:23,201 --> 00:32:24,961
But how did you know that?

676
00:32:25,081 --> 00:32:26,721
He signal led back.

677
00:32:29,081 --> 00:32:30,961
You didn't think
to mention that?

678
00:32:31,081 --> 00:32:32,241
I didn't know it worked.

679
00:32:32,361 --> 00:32:33,481
YAZ: Seriously?

680
00:32:35,801 --> 00:32:38,321
The Skithra have always taken
what we need.

681
00:32:38,441 --> 00:32:39,841
And, Doctor...

682
00:32:41,521 --> 00:32:44,001
...] do not see a need for you.

683
00:32:46,761 --> 00:32:49,801
Oh, is that
a Dullirian resonator?

684
00:32:52,161 --> 00:32:56,241
Oh, and this can power
a starship for months.

685
00:32:56,361 --> 00:32:57,721
You think Tesla's clever?

686
00:32:57,841 --> 00:32:59,281
We make him look like
the village idiot.

687
00:32:59,401 --> 00:33:00,481
A smart,

688
00:33:00,601 --> 00:33:02,961
forward-thinking
scorpion queen like yourself,

689
00:33:03,081 --> 00:33:05,241
I wouldn't go killing
me and Yaz.

690
00:33:05,361 --> 00:33:07,041
Cos Yaz...

691
00:33:07,161 --> 00:33:08,081
(BEEPING)

692
00:33:08,201 --> 00:33:12,601
...can tell you what this is.

693
00:33:12,721 --> 00:33:15,041
- It's a camera.
- Bingo.

694
00:33:15,161 --> 00:33:16,641
(SKITHRA SCREECH)

695
00:33:18,481 --> 00:33:19,681
- GRAHAM: Doctor!
- RYAN: Ah, Yaz.

696
00:33:19,801 --> 00:33:21,361
- Mr Tesla!
- Miss Skerritt.

697
00:33:23,441 --> 00:33:25,601
- (TESLA DRAWS BREATH)
- EDISON: Well, I'll be darned.

698
00:33:25,721 --> 00:33:26,881
She actually got you back.

699
00:33:27,001 --> 00:33:28,121
What is he doing here?

700
00:33:28,241 --> 00:33:29,641
Tesla,

701
00:33:29,761 --> 00:33:30,961
quite a day we're all having.

702
00:33:31,081 --> 00:33:32,321
It's not over yet.

703
00:33:32,441 --> 00:33:33,521
Come on.

704
00:33:33,641 --> 00:33:35,001
This is my private laboratory.

705
00:33:35,121 --> 00:33:36,161
Yes.

706
00:33:37,321 --> 00:33:40,161
You have no right to be he...

707
00:33:40,281 --> 00:33:41,881
What is this?

708
00:33:42,001 --> 00:33:43,801
- Wh... Wh...
- (DOOR CREAKS AND SHUTS)

709
00:33:43,921 --> 00:33:45,561
Where are you all going?

710
00:34:01,121 --> 00:34:03,961
Fantastical!

711
00:34:05,841 --> 00:34:08,121
I couldn't figure it out
either.

712
00:34:08,241 --> 00:34:09,841
The internal dimensions

713
00:34:09,961 --> 00:34:11,481
transcends the external.

714
00:34:11,601 --> 00:34:12,401
Spot-on.

715
00:34:15,121 --> 00:34:16,321
(BUZZING)

716
00:34:17,361 --> 00:34:18,881
Listen up, Skithra queen,

717
00:34:19,001 --> 00:34:21,081
it's me, on behalf of Tesla.

718
00:34:21,201 --> 00:34:23,681
Consider this your official
eviction notice.

719
00:34:23,801 --> 00:34:27,041
Get your ship away from Earth
right now.

720
00:34:27,161 --> 00:34:28,881
QUEEN SKITHRA:
We will take the engineer

721
00:34:29,001 --> 00:34:31,241
or this planet shall burn!

722
00:34:31,361 --> 00:34:34,841
Surrender him
and your lives may be spared.

723
00:34:36,441 --> 00:34:37,641
You can't have him.

724
00:34:37,761 --> 00:34:38,921
He's with us.

725
00:34:39,041 --> 00:34:40,561
And we're not going anywhere.

726
00:34:40,681 --> 00:34:43,841
Then we will kill
all the teeming millions

727
00:34:43,961 --> 00:34:45,001
that infect this world.

728
00:34:45,121 --> 00:34:47,201
And you and your friends
will die first.

729
00:34:47,321 --> 00:34:50,201
This is the choice
you must make.

730
00:34:50,321 --> 00:34:53,281
Give us Tesla, or the planet -

731
00:34:53,401 --> 00:34:56,081
and all who live on it -
shall die.

732
00:34:58,361 --> 00:35:01,161
It cannot be me or the Earth.

733
00:35:02,721 --> 00:35:04,841
You can't place
this burden on me.

734
00:35:07,081 --> 00:35:08,081
Mr Tesla!

735
00:35:08,201 --> 00:35:11,121
(DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES)

736
00:35:12,441 --> 00:35:14,361
(GUTTURAL HISS)

737
00:35:14,481 --> 00:35:16,081
Find them.

738
00:35:31,321 --> 00:35:35,641
I've spent my life wondering
what might be out there.

739
00:35:37,521 --> 00:35:40,601
But creatures who would destroy
the whole planet

740
00:35:40,721 --> 00:35:42,601
just to get their hands on me?

741
00:35:44,161 --> 00:35:46,281
Recognition at last.

742
00:35:47,801 --> 00:35:49,361
(CHUCKLES)

743
00:35:51,361 --> 00:35:52,801
You do realise

744
00:35:52,921 --> 00:35:55,681
it's killing Edison that
they want you and not him.

745
00:35:55,801 --> 00:35:57,201
(EXHALES)

746
00:36:01,401 --> 00:36:04,521
This place, Wardenclyffe...

747
00:36:07,201 --> 00:36:08,721
...] was so close.

748
00:36:08,841 --> 00:36:11,121
People would finally see
what it can do.

749
00:36:11,241 --> 00:36:13,321
What 7 can do.

750
00:36:14,801 --> 00:36:16,241
Now no-one will ever know.

751
00:36:20,121 --> 00:36:21,721
You must all go.

752
00:36:21,841 --> 00:36:23,361
Let them take me.

753
00:36:23,481 --> 00:36:24,881
That's not going to happen.

754
00:36:26,201 --> 00:36:27,441
I have to surrender myself.

755
00:36:27,561 --> 00:36:29,121
There is nothing else
to be done.

756
00:36:29,241 --> 00:36:30,721
This is beyond me.

757
00:36:30,841 --> 00:36:32,561
No.

758
00:36:34,441 --> 00:36:35,361
No?

759
00:36:35,481 --> 00:36:39,401
Nikola Tesla, you're going
to change the world.

760
00:36:41,001 --> 00:36:43,921
But first, you're going
to save it.

761
00:36:44,041 --> 00:36:47,641
Now, tell me all about
Wardenclyffe.

762
00:36:49,321 --> 00:36:50,921
The tower works by harnessing

763
00:36:51,041 --> 00:36:53,361
the electric field
of the Earth itself.

764
00:36:53,481 --> 00:36:56,241
Here - my magnifying
transformer

765
00:36:56,361 --> 00:36:58,361
pumps millions of volts
into this tunnel.

766
00:36:58,481 --> 00:37:01,441
The current races down through
the Earth until it reaches

767
00:37:01,561 --> 00:37:05,321
the other side of the planet,
and then bounces back.

768
00:37:05,441 --> 00:37:07,441
Then it's channel led
into the tower -

769
00:37:07,561 --> 00:37:10,521
wave after wave after wave -
and up into the air!

770
00:37:11,801 --> 00:37:16,041
My intention was to build
a series of these towers...

771
00:37:17,041 --> 00:37:20,201
...transmitting energy
throughout the ether -

772
00:37:20,321 --> 00:37:22,561
a world wireless system.

773
00:37:23,961 --> 00:37:25,241
That's Wi-Fi.

774
00:37:25,361 --> 00:37:27,921
Did Tesla have the idea
for Wi-Fi?

775
00:37:28,041 --> 00:37:29,761
But with enough power,

776
00:37:29,881 --> 00:37:32,921
it could be used to send
a single bolt of lightning

777
00:37:33,041 --> 00:37:34,481
high up into the sky.

778
00:37:34,601 --> 00:37:37,161
Ah, well, if we generate one
large enough,

779
00:37:37,281 --> 00:37:39,681
it could strike the ship,
like so!

780
00:37:39,801 --> 00:37:41,761
Yes! High-five!

781
00:37:43,801 --> 00:37:45,081
Too early!

782
00:37:45,201 --> 00:37:46,721
In a pig's eye.

783
00:37:48,041 --> 00:37:51,201
You want to bet our lives on
a contraption like this, huh?

784
00:37:51,321 --> 00:37:56,481
Some fantastical idea no sane
man would ever invest in?

785
00:38:01,121 --> 00:38:03,241
At least I have ideas.

786
00:38:03,361 --> 00:38:04,921
You have filled a factory
full of men

787
00:38:05,041 --> 00:38:06,681
to do your thinking for you.

788
00:38:06,801 --> 00:38:08,881
Half of your inventions were
thought up by other people.

789
00:38:09,001 --> 00:38:10,241
Anyone can have ideas.

790
00:38:10,361 --> 00:38:12,001
I make them happen.

791
00:38:12,121 --> 00:38:15,441
All those men,
all those inventions,

792
00:38:15,561 --> 00:38:19,321
I turn them from a sketch into
real things people can buy.

793
00:38:19,441 --> 00:38:21,641
That's how you change
the world.

794
00:38:21,761 --> 00:38:25,761
You're too blind to see that
my factory is the best idea

795
00:38:25,881 --> 00:38:27,441
either one of us ever had.

796
00:38:27,561 --> 00:38:30,481
And you are too narrow-minded
to grasp the genius of my work,

797
00:38:30,601 --> 00:38:32,921
and that is why you will never
achieve real greatness.

798
00:38:33,041 --> 00:38:35,961
You are not a man of vision.
You're a man of...parts.

799
00:38:36,081 --> 00:38:39,961
Oi! AC/DC! You two might be
the greatest minds of the age,

800
00:38:40,081 --> 00:38:41,801
but is there any chance
you can stop squabbling

801
00:38:41,921 --> 00:38:43,561
while we try and save
the planet?

802
00:38:45,401 --> 00:38:46,721
We need to move quickly.
We have to prepare the tower.

803
00:38:48,641 --> 00:38:51,201
Here's what
we're going to do...

804
00:38:52,481 --> 00:38:53,801
You and me will finish
the tower.

805
00:38:53,921 --> 00:38:56,041
I can extend the TARDIS shields

806
00:38:56,161 --> 00:38:57,561
within the boundaries
of Wardenclyffe.

807
00:39:00,281 --> 00:39:03,521
That should keep us safe...
for now.

808
00:39:03,641 --> 00:39:07,121
Edison, Yaz - I need you to get
people off the streets.

809
00:39:07,241 --> 00:39:09,201
- The Skithra are on their way.
- (GROWLS AND HISSES)

810
00:39:09,321 --> 00:39:10,881
Dorothy, Graham, Ryan -

811
00:39:11,001 --> 00:39:14,201
find anything we can use
to defend Wardenclyffe.

812
00:39:14,321 --> 00:39:17,201
And be fast. For all we know,
they've already found us.

813
00:39:17,321 --> 00:39:19,881
YAZ: Please! Please!
Everybody inside!

814
00:39:20,001 --> 00:39:21,481
Please! Please move inside.

815
00:39:21,601 --> 00:39:23,481
Everybody inside.

816
00:39:23,601 --> 00:39:25,401
Why is nobody listening to me?
Is it the accent?

817
00:39:25,521 --> 00:39:26,441
Please, it's an emergency!

818
00:39:26,561 --> 00:39:29,601
- Please can you go inside?
- That fool Tesla

819
00:39:29,721 --> 00:39:32,081
is still experimenting
with his deadly tower!

820
00:39:32,201 --> 00:39:35,041
We're as good as fried
if we stay outside.

821
00:39:35,161 --> 00:39:36,921
He's firing it up right now!

822
00:39:37,041 --> 00:39:39,721
- Spread the word!
- (PANICKED SHOUTING)

823
00:39:39,841 --> 00:39:42,761
- No-one is safe!
- (SCREAMING)

824
00:39:43,881 --> 00:39:45,121
(HISSES)

825
00:39:47,121 --> 00:39:48,521
(SIGHS)

826
00:39:48,641 --> 00:39:50,721
"Mechanism for
photographing thoughts"?

827
00:39:50,841 --> 00:39:51,761
- No.
- No.

828
00:39:51,881 --> 00:39:54,281
"Apparatus for producing
ozone."

829
00:39:56,241 --> 00:39:58,561
"Prototype death ray"?

830
00:39:58,681 --> 00:40:00,641
- Yes!
- Yeah?

831
00:40:00,761 --> 00:40:01,801
No, no.

832
00:40:12,401 --> 00:40:14,321
Where is Tesla?

833
00:40:21,881 --> 00:40:24,601
Hey! You stay away from him!

834
00:40:24,721 --> 00:40:26,561
Get down, kid!

835
00:40:28,001 --> 00:40:29,721
Where the hell did he go?

836
00:40:31,401 --> 00:40:32,521
Quick, inside!

837
00:40:36,281 --> 00:40:38,801
- When did you get that?
- Just be glad I did.

838
00:40:38,921 --> 00:40:40,001
- (ZAPPING)
- (GROWLING)

839
00:40:43,561 --> 00:40:45,561
EDISON: Oh, my dear Lord,
what is that?

840
00:40:45,681 --> 00:40:46,921
(SNARLS)

841
00:40:48,241 --> 00:40:50,241
(ROARS)

842
00:40:50,361 --> 00:40:52,121
YAZ: Come on, run!

843
00:40:57,041 --> 00:40:58,441
Run!

844
00:41:12,841 --> 00:41:14,561
(GUNSHOT)

845
00:41:19,681 --> 00:41:21,281
Are you sure this is right?

846
00:41:21,401 --> 00:41:23,441
Tesla said it should be just...
Here!

847
00:41:23,561 --> 00:41:25,401
This tunnel leads us
back to Wardenclyffe.

848
00:41:25,521 --> 00:41:26,561
OK!

849
00:41:35,521 --> 00:41:37,241
Doctor?

850
00:41:37,361 --> 00:41:38,921
We have company.

851
00:41:39,041 --> 00:41:40,801
(SKITHRA SCREECH)

852
00:41:44,641 --> 00:41:46,441
Shield's working, then.

853
00:41:51,361 --> 00:41:53,601
Come on. Come on!

854
00:42:00,081 --> 00:42:02,241
Just in time. We need
to barricade the door now.

855
00:42:02,361 --> 00:42:04,561
- Good God...
- There's too many of them.

856
00:42:04,681 --> 00:42:06,281
Well, they may have
superior numbers,

857
00:42:06,401 --> 00:42:07,841
but we have superior minds.

858
00:42:07,961 --> 00:42:09,441
We just have to hold them off.

859
00:42:09,561 --> 00:42:12,681
They're a hive species.
So if we take out the queen...

860
00:42:12,801 --> 00:42:13,841
We take out all of 'em.

861
00:42:13,961 --> 00:42:15,441
Yes! She's still on the ship,

862
00:42:15,561 --> 00:42:16,921
and, hopefully, we're about
to zap her

863
00:42:17,041 --> 00:42:18,921
with a lot of
Wardenclyffe electricity!

864
00:42:19,041 --> 00:42:20,521
- There's a but.
- Small detail.

865
00:42:20,641 --> 00:42:23,521
Once we power up the tower,
the TARDIS shields will drop,

866
00:42:23,641 --> 00:42:26,361
but it will be about 30 seconds
before we can blast the ship.

867
00:42:26,481 --> 00:42:28,441
There's not enough juice
for both.

868
00:42:28,561 --> 00:42:29,641
What?

869
00:42:29,761 --> 00:42:31,881
What's going to keep them out,
then?

870
00:42:34,441 --> 00:42:35,721
We are.

871
00:42:35,841 --> 00:42:38,041
Don't worry.
This ain't our first rodeo.

872
00:42:38,161 --> 00:42:39,641
We've never been to a rodeo.

873
00:42:39,761 --> 00:42:41,401
You're not helping, Ryan.

874
00:42:42,561 --> 00:42:43,641
Ready?

875
00:42:46,441 --> 00:42:48,161
(DOCTOR GASPS)

876
00:42:59,801 --> 00:43:01,761
It's working.

877
00:43:01,881 --> 00:43:03,961
DOCTOR: The tower's charging.

878
00:43:05,241 --> 00:43:07,401
Nearly there.

879
00:43:07,521 --> 00:43:09,241
Get ready out there.

880
00:43:09,361 --> 00:43:11,721
Shields are about to drop.

881
00:43:16,881 --> 00:43:19,321
Shields down.
A few more seconds.

882
00:43:19,441 --> 00:43:22,321
GRAHAM: We ain't got
a few seconds, Doc!

883
00:43:22,441 --> 00:43:24,201
(RATTLING)

884
00:43:25,241 --> 00:43:28,281
What? Signal coming
from the Skithra ship.

885
00:43:35,641 --> 00:43:37,481
(SKITHRA SCREECH)

886
00:43:37,601 --> 00:43:40,081
(SCREECHING FADES)

887
00:43:40,201 --> 00:43:42,001
What are they doing?

888
00:43:42,121 --> 00:43:44,561
Why aren't they attacking?

889
00:43:44,681 --> 00:43:45,881
Oh, no.

890
00:43:46,001 --> 00:43:47,321
What is it?

891
00:43:51,321 --> 00:43:53,441
Let's see what this thing
can do.

892
00:43:53,561 --> 00:43:54,761
Stay out of our lab!

893
00:43:59,161 --> 00:44:00,321
We can't blast the ship -

894
00:44:00,441 --> 00:44:02,361
because the queen's
no longer on it.

895
00:44:10,081 --> 00:44:11,881
(GASPS)

896
00:44:18,121 --> 00:44:19,721
This was not the plan.

897
00:44:19,841 --> 00:44:22,801
Was this meant to be
your fortress?

898
00:44:22,921 --> 00:44:25,161
And you its defenders?

899
00:44:26,681 --> 00:44:28,641
What was the plan?

900
00:44:28,761 --> 00:44:31,881
To shiver in the dark
until we went away?

901
00:44:32,001 --> 00:44:33,121
(SNARLS)

902
00:44:33,241 --> 00:44:35,201
(GASPS)

903
00:44:35,321 --> 00:44:37,921
Oh, you really are fragile
creatures, aren't you?

904
00:44:38,041 --> 00:44:40,321
It's a miracle
your world has spun on

905
00:44:40,441 --> 00:44:42,041
so long undisturbed.

906
00:44:43,681 --> 00:44:44,681
Now, tell me.

907
00:44:44,801 --> 00:44:46,041
Where is he?

908
00:44:48,281 --> 00:44:49,641
No?

909
00:44:49,761 --> 00:44:51,481
Then which of you would like

910
00:44:51,601 --> 00:44:54,761
- the privilege of dying first?
- DOCTOR: Stop!

911
00:44:54,881 --> 00:44:57,521
If you want Tesla,
you have to go through me.

912
00:44:57,641 --> 00:45:00,441
Doctor, did you really think

913
00:45:00,561 --> 00:45:02,321
I'd let you hide away
down here,

914
00:45:02,441 --> 00:45:04,161
hatching your little plans?

915
00:45:04,281 --> 00:45:06,761
If I'd known we were going
to have a royal visit,

916
00:45:06,881 --> 00:45:08,161
I'd have put the kettle on.

917
00:45:08,281 --> 00:45:10,721
As queen, I grant myself
the pleasure of killing you...

918
00:45:10,841 --> 00:45:12,881
(INHALES SHARPLY)
...in person.

919
00:45:13,001 --> 00:45:16,761
And what are you
queen of, exactly?

920
00:45:16,881 --> 00:45:18,721
A stolen ship
and second-hand guns?

921
00:45:18,841 --> 00:45:21,681
A queen of shreds and patches.

922
00:45:21,801 --> 00:45:24,441
You're not a ruler,
you're a parasite.

923
00:45:24,561 --> 00:45:25,841
And what are you?

924
00:45:25,961 --> 00:45:28,841
So clever,
stealing onto my ship,

925
00:45:28,961 --> 00:45:30,641
taking what I claimed as mine.

926
00:45:31,681 --> 00:45:33,561
But where has it got you?

927
00:45:33,681 --> 00:45:34,601
No weapons.

928
00:45:34,721 --> 00:45:36,041
No arm our.

929
00:45:36,161 --> 00:45:37,841
No escape.

930
00:45:37,961 --> 00:45:41,721
Just the desperate hope
you might change my mind.

931
00:45:41,841 --> 00:45:44,881
No. We're way past that.
I gave you your chance.

932
00:45:45,001 --> 00:45:48,481
- A chance to be like you?
- A chance to evolve.

933
00:45:48,601 --> 00:45:50,481
But you were too stupid
to take it.

934
00:45:51,561 --> 00:45:53,881
When you die, there'll be
nothing left behind.

935
00:45:54,001 --> 00:45:56,761
Just a trail of blood
and other people's brilliance.

936
00:45:56,881 --> 00:45:58,961
No-one will even know
you existed.

937
00:45:59,081 --> 00:46:00,761
(HISSES)

938
00:46:00,881 --> 00:46:02,881
It's important you understand,
Doctor,

939
00:46:03,001 --> 00:46:05,961
that we would have only taken
the engineer.

940
00:46:06,081 --> 00:46:08,961
Now, because of you,

941
00:46:09,081 --> 00:46:10,881
I will take everything.

942
00:46:11,961 --> 00:46:15,201
We will overrun this world
and pick the bones clean.

943
00:46:15,321 --> 00:46:17,921
Have you ever seen
a dead planet?

944
00:46:19,841 --> 00:46:23,281
I've seen more
than you can possibly imagine.

945
00:46:23,401 --> 00:46:24,641
And yet you still think

946
00:46:24,761 --> 00:46:26,921
I can be fooled
by the same trick twice.

947
00:46:27,041 --> 00:46:28,001
(GASPS)

948
00:46:28,121 --> 00:46:29,561
- Doctor!
- Stay back!

949
00:46:29,681 --> 00:46:31,201
(SNARLS)

950
00:46:33,481 --> 00:46:36,561
A final weapon
for our collection.

951
00:46:36,681 --> 00:46:40,241
And what were you planning
to do with this?

952
00:46:42,441 --> 00:46:44,441
Nothing. I just wanted you
to take it.

953
00:46:44,561 --> 00:46:46,721
(SCREWDRIVER BUZZES)

954
00:46:46,841 --> 00:46:48,521
(ROARS)

955
00:46:48,641 --> 00:46:50,001
Tesla, now!

956
00:46:50,121 --> 00:46:51,201
Press the switch!

957
00:46:59,481 --> 00:47:01,241
(SKITHRA ROAR)

958
00:47:27,761 --> 00:47:29,601
There you go, kid.

959
00:47:29,721 --> 00:47:31,321
Thank you.

960
00:47:37,921 --> 00:47:40,321
I gotta hand it to you.

961
00:47:40,441 --> 00:47:41,681
You did it.

962
00:47:45,601 --> 00:47:47,361
Come work for me again.

963
00:47:50,841 --> 00:47:52,601
You keep working on this thing,

964
00:47:52,721 --> 00:47:54,641
you'll be bankrupt
within the year.

965
00:47:55,841 --> 00:47:57,121
Perhaps.

966
00:47:58,121 --> 00:47:59,801
But how could I stop now?

967
00:48:02,641 --> 00:48:04,081
(CHUCKLES)

968
00:48:05,841 --> 00:48:06,841
You take good care
of yourself.

969
00:48:06,961 --> 00:48:07,961
You too.

970
00:48:08,081 --> 00:48:11,441
Was that more or less
impossible than your usual day?

971
00:48:11,561 --> 00:48:14,321
Yeah, about average. You?

972
00:48:14,441 --> 00:48:16,201
Slightly stranger.

973
00:48:17,401 --> 00:48:20,241
Normal would be boring,
wouldn't it?

974
00:48:21,441 --> 00:48:22,881
Bye.

975
00:48:25,321 --> 00:48:28,841
Now, this all changes, right?
The protests, the funding.

976
00:48:28,961 --> 00:48:30,801
Tesla's tower's just saved
the world!

977
00:48:30,921 --> 00:48:32,601
That's gotta mean
rich and famous.

978
00:48:32,721 --> 00:48:33,641
No.

979
00:48:33,761 --> 00:48:35,281
Nothing's changed.

980
00:48:35,401 --> 00:48:37,921
A few years from now
Wardenclyffe is torn down.

981
00:48:38,041 --> 00:48:42,841
Tesla keeps on inventing,
but no money, no fame.

982
00:48:42,961 --> 00:48:46,241
He dies penniless.
History leaves him behind.

983
00:48:46,361 --> 00:48:49,041
But his vision of wireless
energy, that does happen,

984
00:48:49,161 --> 00:48:50,721
a connected world,

985
00:48:50,841 --> 00:48:53,201
and that idea starts here,
with him.

986
00:48:53,321 --> 00:48:54,521
That's not right.

987
00:48:54,641 --> 00:48:55,721
People should know.

988
00:48:55,841 --> 00:48:58,401
Either way, it doesn't change
what he's done.

989
00:48:58,521 --> 00:48:59,841
Doctor...

990
00:48:59,961 --> 00:49:02,441
You have to let me study
that machine of yours.

991
00:49:02,561 --> 00:49:04,761
It is by far the most
magnificent invention

992
00:49:04,881 --> 00:49:06,521
I've ever seen in my life.

993
00:49:06,641 --> 00:49:08,561
Never mind the TARDIS,

994
00:49:08,681 --> 00:49:11,121
you've got enough magnificent
inventions of your own.

995
00:49:12,361 --> 00:49:14,041
Yes. Yes, you're right.

996
00:49:14,161 --> 00:49:16,841
You're right, of course.
There's so much to be done.

997
00:49:18,881 --> 00:49:20,521
Thank you.

998
00:49:21,921 --> 00:49:23,641
Thank you, all.

999
00:49:23,761 --> 00:49:25,281
Don't give up.

1000
00:49:25,401 --> 00:49:27,081
Whatever anyone says.

1001
00:49:28,561 --> 00:49:30,201
Well, let them talk.

1002
00:49:30,321 --> 00:49:32,001
The present is theirs.

1003
00:49:32,121 --> 00:49:33,681
I work for the future.

1004
00:49:36,361 --> 00:49:38,241
And the future is mine.

1005
00:49:45,681 --> 00:49:47,441
Shall we?

1006
00:50:22,001 --> 00:50:23,441
A Judoon warning transmission.

1007
00:50:24,561 --> 00:50:25,521
Who are you?

1008
00:50:25,641 --> 00:50:27,241
The city's under siege.

1009
00:50:28,281 --> 00:50:30,881
- Do you trust me, Ruth?
- Sometimes.

